The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | All-party, but no Mamata
                                                                                                               All-party, but no Mamata
                            
	Calcutta, June 5: Ravaged by political and natural calamities, chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee and his party today decided to call an all-party meeting on Sunday to discuss cyclone relief.        
	A CPM state secretariat huddle this morning decided on the meeting, to be held at Writers Buildings.         
	Mamata Banerjee, however, said in Delhi that her party would not go there to put its seal of approval on the disaster brought about by the state governments shoddy relief operations.        
	The CPM, however, will go ahead with the meeting despite the Trinamul no-show. We took the initiative to show a spirit of co-operation in the time of calamity. People will see how Mamata reacts, said a secretariat member.                                                                                                                                                                              
